FAQs about hotels in Pittsburgh

On average, 3-star hotels in Pittsburgh cost $158 per night, and 4-star hotels in Pittsburgh are $181 per night. If you're looking for something really special, a 5-star hotel in Pittsburgh can be found for $268 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
The average price per night for a 3-star hotel in Pittsburgh this weekend is $200 or, for a 4-star hotel, $204. Looking for something even fancier? 5-star hotels in Pittsburgh for this weekend cost around $278 per night, on average (based on Booking.com prices).
On average, it costs $171 per night to book a 3-star hotel in Pittsburgh for tonight. You'll pay around $195 if you choose to stay in a 4-star hotel tonight, while a 5-star hotel in Pittsburgh will cost around $272, on average (based on Booking.com prices).

  • Review score
    10.0

    Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, is celebrated for its extensive...

    Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania, is celebrated for its extensive network of bridges and rivers, as well as its iconic highway tunnels, including the Liberty Tunnels, Fort Pitt Tunnel, and Squirrel Hill Tunnel. The city boasts world-class museums and prestigious institutions such as the University of Pittsburgh (Pitt) and Carnegie Mellon University. A standout landmark is the Cathedral of Learning, an architectural marvel with a steel frame encased in Indiana limestone. Serving as the main classroom and administrative hub for Pitt, this historic structure is also listed on the National Register of Historic Places.
    Guest review by
